

-static is keyword in java
-static means fix (only one copy is created)
-In Java, static means something belongs to the class, not to the object.
-there are three use of static 
  1) static varible
  2) static method
  3) static block
---------------------------------------------------------
1) static varible
 - only one copy is created.
 - use for auto increment.

* syntax--> static datatype varible;
* Example-->static int a;
---------------------------------------------------------
--------------------------------------------------------

2) static method(call without object)
 -Static method can be called using the class name.
 -It cannot access non-static (normal) variables directly.
----------------------------------------------------------
* calling static method
1) directly calling witthout class and object
--> add(11,22);

2) using class name
-->classname.function_name(value)
-->demo.add(11,33);

3) using object
-->object_name.function_name(value);
--> ob.add(100,44);
---------------------------------------------------------
 * syntax--> static returntype methodname(arg list)
             {
              //code
             }
 * Example-->

      class MyClass {
    static void greet() {
        System.out.println("Hello!");
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        MyClass.greet();  // No object needed
    }
}
---------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------
3) static block
 -Static block runs automatically when the class is loaded.
 -It runs before the main method.
* syntax
--> static{
            //code
         }
